statement.tex:
\text{Find all the points of discontinuity of f(x),\\
where f(x) is defined by}\\

f(x) = \begin{cases} 
         \frac{x}{\vert x \vert}, x\lt 0\\
         -1, x\geq 0
         \end{cases}

step.reason:
\begin{align}
  \text{When }x &\lt 0, \vert x\vert = -x \implies\dfrac{x}{\vert x\vert} = -1 
\end{align} \\
\text{And for }x\geq 0,\text{ we are told }f(x) = -1.\\
\text{Hence, }
f(x) = \begin{cases}
  -1, x\lt 0, \\  
  -1, x\geq 0
\end{cases} = \begin{cases} -1\text{ for all } x.\end{cases}
